Useful Git Command

# Basic Commands:

* git init (initlizing git repository)
* rm -rf .git (remove git directory)

* git clone <repo url> (clone remote repo to local repo)
* git clone <repo> <directory>


* git add . (adding all untracked files)
* git add <file-name> (add untracked files by name)

* git commit -m <"your message"> (commit alreday added files)
* git commit -a -m <"your message"> (add and commit modified files)

* git push -u <remote_name> <local_branch_name> (git push -u origin master -> pushing staged changes to remote repo)


* git reset <commit-id> (reset your git directory to a commit)


# Git Branch:

* git branch --help 
* git branch <branch_name> (create new branch)
* git branch (git branch -l/--list -> list name of all branches)
* git branch -d <branch_name> (delete a branch)
* git branch -m <branch> (rename a branch)
* git checkout <branch_name> (switch to a branch)


# Git Remote:

* git remote --help
* git remote add <remote_name> <remote_repo_url> (add remote to local git repo)
* git remote add origin <remote_repo_url> 
* git remote show origin
* git remote remove origin 

# Git Config:

* git config --global credential.helper store (add user configuration to git repo)
* git config --global user.name <"your username"> (add username to git config)
* git config --global user.password <"your password"> (add password to git config)
* git config -l (list out git configurations)
* git config --list (list out git configurations)
* git config --global -l/--list (list out git global config)

